1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 32-12.1 of the North Dakota
2 Century Code, relating to the medical liability of a government entity.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. A new section to chapter 32-12.1 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
5 and enacted as follows:
6 Medical liability of government entity.
7 1. As used in this section, "medical product" means a product used to diagnose or
8 manage a disease, including a medical device, drug, or biologic.
9 2. Notwithstanding any other provision of law, a state agency, political subdivision, or any
10 other government entity, may not require an individual to take, receive, or disclose
11 whether the individual has taken or received a medical product unless the
12 manufacturer of the medical product is liable for any death or serious injury caused by
13 the medical product.
